# Champions directory
#
# Champion profiles are NEVER committed to the repo — they contain personal data
# (Slack user IDs, writing samples, email, inspirations, feedback history).
#
# Each operator builds their own champions locally via the /new-champion command:
#
#     /new-champion @dor.blech role:comms
#
# This creates:
#     champions/dor-blech/
#     ├── profile.json
#     ├── tone-of-voice.md
#     ├── style-preferences.md
#     ├── rules.md
#     ├── inspirations.md
#     └── content-history/
#
# The .gitignore blocks champions/* but keeps this .gitkeep so the directory
# exists in fresh clones.
#
# If you need to share a champion profile across machines, use the Base44
# backend (see docs/plans/2026-03-31-backend-design.md) which stores profiles
# as entities in a shared Champion table. Local files are cache-only.
